{{Infobox settlement | name = Khora | native_name = Khora Colony | native_name_lang = | settlement_type = | image_skyline = | image_alt = | image_caption = | nickname = | pushpin_map = India Uttar Pradesh#India | pushpin_label_position = right | pushpin_map_alt = | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Uttar Pradesh, India | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = {{flag|India}} | subdivision_type1 = [[States and territories of India|State]] | subdivision_name1 = [[Uttar Pradesh]] | subdivision_type2 = [[List of districts of India|District]] | subdivision_name2 = [[Ghaziabad district, India|Ghaziabad]] | subdivision_type3 = [[Administrative divisions of Uttar Pradesh|Administrative Division]] | subdivision_name3 = [[Meerut division]] | established_title = | established_date = | named_for = | government_type = | governing_body = | unit_pref = Metric | area_footnotes = | area_total_km2 = 10 | area_rank = | elevation_footnotes = | elevation_m = 212 | population_footnotes = | population_total = 190,005 | population_as_of = 2011 | population_rank = | population_density_km2 = 19000 | population_demonym = | demographics_type1 = Languages | demographics1_title1 = Official | demographics1_info1 = [[Hindi language|Hindi]] | timezone1 = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]] | utc_offset1 = +5:30 | postal_code_type = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]] | postal_code = 201001 | area_code_type = Telephone code | area_code = 0120 | registration_plate = up14 | blank1_name_sec1 = [[Lok Sabha]] Constituency | blank1_info_sec1 = [[Sahibabad]] | blank2_name_sec1 = Nearest city | blank2_info_sec1 = [[Indirapuram]] | website = {{URL|www.npploni.in}} | footnotes = }} '''Khora''' is a town in the [[Ghaziabad district, India|Ghaziabad district]] of [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.census2011.co.in/census/city/106-khora.html|title=Khora City Population Census 2011 {{!}} Uttar Pradesh|website=www.census2011.co.in|access-date=2018-09-15}}</ref> Its official census population is approximately 190,000 residents (2011),<ref name=":0" /> but reports<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/955138429|title=Accumulation in post-colonial capitalism|last=|first=|publisher=|others=Mitra, Iman Kumar,, Samāddāra, Raṇabīra,, Sen, Samita|year=|isbn=9811010374|location=Singapore|pages=109–123|oclc=955138429}}</ref> suggest a population closer to 1,000,000 residents inside the city's area of 10 square kilometers. It is located the on [[NH-24]] highway, near [[Gaziabad]] and [[Delhi]], and is within the [[National Capital Region (India)|National Capital Region of India]]. It is bound on the west and southwest by the village of [[Ghazipur (Delhi)|Ghazipur]], on the north and northwest by [[Hindon River|Hindon Canal]], on the northeast by [[Ghaziabad, Uttar Pradesh#Demographics|Indirapuram (Ghaizabad)]], and on the east and southeast by [[Noida]]. The Chairman of Khora is Reena Bhati<ref>https://www.jagran.com/uttar-pradesh/ghaziabad-khoda-chairman-Naveen-sharma-17130855.html</ref>.
==Accessibility== It is connected by road to [[NH 24]], and by rail to [[Anand Vihar Railway Station]], While Anand Vihar is closer, the [[Ghaziabad Junction railway station]] (9&nbsp;km) and [[Hazrat Nizamuddin Railway Station]] (10&nbsp;km) are also proximate. It is also linked to [[Vaishali (Ghaziabad)|Vaishali Station]] and [[Kaushambi metro station|Kaushambi Station]] by metro.
